 {"id":"bd-wcv-epic","title":"PORT: wcstol/wcstoul wide-char number parsing to core::stdlib::conversion","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T00:54:12.807307Z","description":"wchar_abi.rs duplicates ~180 lines of base/sign/prefix/digit-accumulation logic that already lives in core::stdlib::conversion::strtol_impl / strtoul_impl, but on &[u32] instead of &[u8]. Plus three local helpers (wide_is_space, wide_digit_value, wide_is_ascii_hexdigit) replicate stdlib utilities. Lift the wide variants into core::stdlib::conversion alongside the byte versions, sharing the existing ConversionStatus enum.","updated_at":"2026-04-25T00:59:40.135727Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T00:59:40.135727Z","close_reason":"Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. Net effect: ~205 lines of inline base/sign/prefix/digit-accumulation parsing in wchar_abi.rs (parse_wide_signed + parse_wide_unsigned + 3 helpers) replaced by ~205 lines of pure-safe core::stdlib::conversion wide-char parsers (wcstol_impl + wcstoul_impl + 3 helpers) sitting beside the existing strtol_impl/strtoul_impl byte versions, sharing the same ConversionStatus enum. The 3 parity tests in core prove byte/wide implementations stay in lockstep; future fixes to one half are testable against the other."}
 {"id":"bd-wcv-1","title":"PORT: wcstol/wcstoul sub-bead 1 \u2014 core wide-char number parsers","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-wcv-epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T00:54:12.807307Z","description":"Add to core::stdlib::conversion: pub fn wcstol_impl(s: &[u32], base: i32) -> (i64, usize, ConversionStatus); pub fn wcstoul_impl(s: &[u32], base: i32) -> (u64, usize, ConversionStatus); pub fn wide_is_space(wc: u32) -> bool; pub fn wide_digit_value(wc: u32) -> Option<u32>. Logic must be 1:1 with strtol_impl / strtoul_impl: leading whitespace skip, optional +/- sign, base==0 auto-detect (0x\u219216, 0\u21928, else 10), base==16 + 0x prefix consumed, base in 2..=36 validation, accumulator overflow handling, negative-overflow becomes Underflow, positive becomes Overflow. Tests: i64::MAX/MIN round-trip, u64::MAX round-trip, base detection (0x, 0, plain), negative numbers, sign+empty, whitespace skip, invalid base, overflow/underflow status, mid-digit base mismatch, parity with strtol_impl/strtoul_impl on ASCII inputs.","updated_at":"2026-04-25T00:59:40.135727Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T00:59:40.135727Z","close_reason":"Added to core::stdlib::conversion: pub fn wide_is_space(wc: u32) -> bool (Unicode-aware whitespace recognition via char::from_u32().is_whitespace()); pub fn wide_digit_value(wc: u32) -> Option<u32> (matches strtol digit-table semantics for ASCII 0-9/a-z/A-Z); pub fn wcstol_impl(s: &[u32], base: i32) -> (i64, usize, ConversionStatus) and pub fn wcstoul_impl structurally identical to the byte-slice strtol_impl/strtoul_impl. All four share the existing ConversionStatus enum (no duplication). 31 unit tests cover Unicode whitespace recognition, digit-value mapping, base 0 auto-detect (0x->16, 0->8, else 10), explicit base 16 + 0x prefix, base 2..=36 validation, sign-only/empty/whitespace-only edge cases, overflow/underflow status reporting, mid-digit base mismatch, plus 3 parity tests proving wcstol_impl/wcstoul_impl produce IDENTICAL (value, consumed, status) tuples vs strtol_impl/strtoul_impl on ASCII inputs across a dozen cases including i64::MAX/MIN, u64::MAX/overflow, base 0/16/36/8."}
 {"id":"bd-wcv-2","title":"PORT: wcstol/wcstoul sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi shims","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-wcv-epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T00:54:12.807307Z","description":"Drop wide_is_space, wide_digit_value, wide_is_ascii_hexdigit, parse_wide_signed, parse_wide_unsigned (~205 lines total) from wchar_abi.rs. wcstol/wcstoll/wcstoimax delegate to core::stdlib::conversion::wcstol_impl. wcstoul/wcstoull/wcstoumax delegate to wcstoul_impl. ConversionStatus stays the same enum (already shared). Verify all wcstol/wcstoul tests still pass.","updated_at":"2026-04-25T00:59:40.135727Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T00:59:40.135727Z","close_reason":"Removed wide_is_space, wide_digit_value, wide_is_ascii_hexdigit, parse_wide_signed, parse_wide_unsigned (~205 lines total) from frankenlibc-abi/src/wchar_abi.rs. wcstol shim now calls frankenlibc_core::stdlib::conversion::wcstol_impl; wcstoul calls wcstoul_impl. ConversionStatus continues to be imported from core (it was already a shared type). Verified via rch with CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_target_frankenlibc_cc_bd-wcv-2: 173/173 abi lib tests pass; 107/107 wchar integration + conformance tests pass; cargo clippy -D warnings clean on both core+abi; cargo fmt --check clean."}
-{"id": "bd-cat-epic", "title": "PORT: GNU catgets binary catalog parser to core::locale::catgets", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z", "description": "Lift parse_catalog_bytes (~65 lines) and MessageCatalog struct + message_ptr lookup from frankenlibc-abi/src/locale_abi.rs into core::locale::catgets. Pure binary-format parsing \u2014 magic detection (LE/BE swap), header word reads, two-table layout, plane hash lookup. Format: 3-word header (magic + plane_size + plane_depth), 2 tables of plane_size*plane_depth*3 words each, then strings blob. Sub-bead 1: add the parser + lookup_message_offset(set_id, msg_id) -> Option<usize> (returning string-blob offset rather than raw pointer to keep core in #![deny(unsafe_code)]). Sub-bead 2: rewire abi to delegate."}
-{"id":"bd-cat-1","title":"PORT: catgets sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::locale::catgets module","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-cat-epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T02:28:50Z","description":"Add crates/frankenlibc-core/src/locale/catgets.rs with: CATGETS_MAGIC: u32 = 0x9604_08de; pub const CATALOG_HEADER_WORDS = 3; CATALOG_SLOT_WORDS = 3; pub enum CatalogParseError (InvalidMagic, TruncatedHeader, ZeroPlane, ArithmeticOverflow, TruncatedTable, MissingNul); pub struct MessageCatalog { plane_size, plane_depth, table: Box<[u32]>, strings: Box<[u8]> }; pub fn parse_catalog_bytes(bytes: Vec<u8>) -> Result<MessageCatalog, CatalogParseError>; impl MessageCatalog { pub fn message_offset(&self, set_id: i32, msg_id: i32) -> Option<usize>; pub fn message_bytes(&self, set_id: i32, msg_id: i32) -> Option<&[u8]> } where the latter returns the NUL-terminated message slice (without the NUL). Tests: synthesized minimal catalog (1 set, 1 msg), magic LE/BE detection, plane_size==0 / plane_depth==0 rejection, arithmetic overflow rejection, table truncation rejection, missing trailing NUL rejection, lookup hit/miss, hash-collision walk through plane_depth slots.","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc"}
-{"id": "bd-cat-2", "title": "PORT: catgets sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi catgets shims", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-cat-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z", "description": "Drop parse_catalog_bytes + MessageCatalog struct + message_ptr method from locale_abi.rs. catopen / catgets / catclose now wrap core::locale::catgets::MessageCatalog (or a registry of it). The abi keeps the nl_catd descriptor allocator + global Mutex<CatalogRegistry> + the CString fallback synthesis for catalog NULL-pointer paths. Verify catgets/catopen abi tests pass."}
-{"id": "bd-cat-1", "title": "PORT: catgets sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::locale::catgets module", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-cat-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "resolution": "Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/locale/catgets.rs with: pub const CATGETS_MAGIC=0x9604_08de, CATALOG_HEADER_WORDS=3, CATALOG_SLOT_WORDS=3; pub enum CatalogParseError (InvalidMagic, TruncatedHeader, ZeroPlane, ArithmeticOverflow, TruncatedTable, MissingNul); pub struct MessageCatalog { plane_size, plane_depth, table: Box<[u32]>, strings: Box<[u8]> }; pub fn parse_catalog_bytes(bytes) -> Result<MessageCatalog, CatalogParseError> with bidirectional magic detection (LE/BE), checked arithmetic for plane footprint, table chunks_exact, NUL-termination check on max-offset string; impl MessageCatalog { pub fn message_offset(set_id, msg_id) -> Option<usize>; pub fn message_bytes(set_id, msg_id) -> Option<&[u8]> }. 14 unit tests cover minimal catalog round-trip, magic LE+BE detection, header truncation, plane_size==0, plane_depth==0, plane overflow rejection, buffer truncation, header-only buffer, missing-message lookup, negative msg_id rejection, hash collision walk through plane_depth slots, message_offset blob-index returns valid range, message_bytes excludes NUL, slot offset past blob rejected."}
-{"id": "bd-cat-2", "title": "PORT: catgets sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi catgets shims", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-cat-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "resolution": "Removed CATGETS_MAGIC / CATALOG_HEADER_WORDS / CATALOG_SLOT_WORDS / MessageCatalog struct + impl message_ptr / catalog_word / parse_catalog_bytes (~140 lines) from locale_abi.rs. catopen now calls a thin parse_catalog_bytes wrapper that maps CatalogParseError \u2192 libc::EINVAL preserving the existing errno semantics. catgets calls catalog.message_offset(set_id, msg_id) and constructs the *const c_char from the catalog strings blob at the boundary. CatalogRegistry / next_catalog_id / nl_catd descriptor allocator stay in abi where they have to be. Side-fix: corrected pre-existing let-Some-else syntax errors in wchar_abi.rs that the linter pass had introduced. Verified via rch with CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_target_frankenlibc_cc_bd-cat-2: 173/173 abi lib + 50/50 locale_abi integration tests pass; cargo clippy -D warnings clean; cargo fmt --check clean."}
-{"id": "bd-cat-epic", "title": "PORT: GNU catgets binary catalog parser to core::locale::catgets", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z", "resolution": "Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. Net effect: ~140 lines of pure binary-format parsing in locale_abi.rs (parse_catalog_bytes + MessageCatalog + message_ptr + helpers + 4 const definitions) replaced by ~210 lines of pure-safe core::locale::catgets with 14 isolation-tested cases plus typed CatalogParseError. The catalog parser is now reachable from any caller and lives behind #![deny(unsafe_code)]. Side fix: pre-existing wchar_abi.rs let-Some-else syntax errors corrected."}
